WEBVTT

00:00:12.667 --> 00:00:14.417
What are you talking about?

00:00:16.125 --> 00:00:18.042
"February 23, 2024"       "Floor 35: Lost Forest"
You've got that lizard to heal you.

00:00:18.042 --> 00:00:20.708
"February 23, 2024"       "Floor 35: Lost Forest"
We shouldn't have to share
these heal crystals with you!

00:00:21.833 --> 00:00:24.750
Well, you never fight
on the front lines!

00:00:24.750 --> 00:00:26.208
And you still need crystals?

00:00:26.208 --> 00:00:28.208
Of course I do...

00:00:28.208 --> 00:00:30.750
I'm not a child idol
like you, Silica,

00:00:30.750 --> 00:00:33.583
so it's not as if the
boys will heal me.

00:00:34.500 --> 00:00:36.792
C-Come on, you two...

00:00:36.792 --> 00:00:38.125
Fine!

00:00:38.125 --> 00:00:39.625
I don't need any items.

00:00:39.625 --> 00:00:42.083
I'm never going to
team up with you again!

00:00:42.083 --> 00:00:46.125
There are plenty of other parties
that want me, you know!

00:00:46.583 --> 00:00:50.083
H-Hey, Silica!

00:01:01.417 --> 00:01:05.833
<i>The cowardly past that I'd acknowledged</i>

00:01:06.167 --> 00:01:11.667
<i>Still not understanding why,</i>

00:01:12.000 --> 00:01:22.542
<i>I stand behind myself, scared</i>
<i>Projecting reality onto today</i>

00:01:22.917 --> 00:01:27.917
<i>I've drawn so many skies</i>

00:01:28.250 --> 00:01:32.625
<i>This must be my fleeting heart</i>

00:01:32.958 --> 00:01:35.333
<i>Out of control</i>

00:01:35.667 --> 00:01:40.917
<i>In my dreams, this body soars so high</i>

00:01:41.250 --> 00:01:46.083
<i>And it can brush away any fears that cling to me</i>

00:01:46.417 --> 00:01:52.583
<i>Asleep inside me, these budding</i>
<i>feelings start to expand</i>

00:01:52.917 --> 00:01:56.542
<i>I realize this, weak as I am...</i>
<i>As long as I had you</i>

00:01:56.917 --> 00:02:01.875
<i>I could stay strong in this dark world</i>

00:02:02.208 --> 00:02:07.875
<i>My heart will dream a long dream forever</i>

00:02:08.792 --> 00:02:11.250
<i>I want to always be with you</i>

00:02:11.583 --> 00:02:16.958
<i>I'll give you everything I have...</i>

00:02:20.042 --> 00:02:24.042
"The Black Swordsman"

00:02:46.167 --> 00:02:47.792
<i>No healing items?!</i>

00:03:05.375 --> 00:03:06.833
Pina!

00:03:06.833 --> 00:03:08.333
Pina... Pina!

00:03:09.750 --> 00:03:10.750
Pina.

00:03:12.708 --> 00:03:13.833
Pina...

00:03:16.375 --> 00:03:18.333
Pina...

00:03:18.333 --> 00:03:19.375
Pina!

00:03:19.375 --> 00:03:21.667
Pina... Pina!

00:03:54.125 --> 00:03:55.125
Pina...

00:03:56.792 --> 00:03:59.333
Don't leave me all alone.

00:04:00.042 --> 00:04:01.250
Pina!

00:04:05.458 --> 00:04:06.792
What's that feather?

00:04:08.125 --> 00:04:09.167
It's Pina.

00:04:10.750 --> 00:04:12.500
My dear...

00:04:13.708 --> 00:04:15.917
You're a beast tamer?

00:04:16.625 --> 00:04:18.000
I'm sorry...

00:04:18.500 --> 00:04:21.167
I wasn't able to save your friend.

00:04:21.583 --> 00:04:22.875
No...

00:04:22.875 --> 00:04:24.833
...it was stupid of me.

00:04:24.833 --> 00:04:28.875
For thinking that I could make it through the
forest on my own... for being so arrogant!

00:04:30.208 --> 00:04:33.208
Thank you so much...
for saving me.

00:04:33.625 --> 00:04:37.625
Does that feather happen
to have an item name?

00:04:40.958 --> 00:04:43.042
"Pina's Heart"

00:04:46.500 --> 00:04:47.625
Don't cry.

00:04:47.625 --> 00:04:51.500
If Pina's Heart is still here,
there's a chance you can revive it.

00:04:52.875 --> 00:04:54.375
Really?

00:04:55.250 --> 00:04:56.875
On the south side of floor 47,

00:04:57.250 --> 00:04:59.792
there's a field dungeon
called the Hill of Memories.

00:05:00.458 --> 00:05:04.625
I've heard that the flower that blooms
at its top is an item for reviving familiars.

00:05:08.000 --> 00:05:09.583
Floor 47...

00:05:10.958 --> 00:05:14.542
If you cover my expenses,
I'd be glad to go for you...

00:05:15.000 --> 00:05:19.042
But the familiar's master has to be there
or the flower won't bloom.

00:05:19.042 --> 00:05:21.583
I'm very grateful just to
have the information!

00:05:22.000 --> 00:05:24.583
If I work hard to raise my level,
then someday...

00:05:24.583 --> 00:05:27.250
Pina can only be resurrected up to
three days after its death.

00:05:28.917 --> 00:05:30.167
No way...

00:05:31.042 --> 00:05:32.417
All because of me...

00:05:33.625 --> 00:05:35.458
I'm so sorry, Pina.

00:05:36.417 --> 00:05:37.500
Don't worry.

00:05:37.500 --> 00:05:38.500
You have three days.

00:05:40.792 --> 00:05:44.292
This equipment should be good
for a boost of five or six levels.

00:05:44.292 --> 00:05:47.292
If I go with you, I think
it should all work out.

00:05:49.208 --> 00:05:52.500
Why would you do
all this for me?

00:05:55.542 --> 00:05:59.083
If you promise not to
laugh, I'll tell you.

00:05:59.792 --> 00:06:01.042
I won't laugh.

00:06:03.667 --> 00:06:07.042
It's because you look
like my little sister...

00:06:15.333 --> 00:06:16.375
I'm sorry.

00:06:18.917 --> 00:06:22.625
Um, I'm sure this isn't
enough to cover it, but...

00:06:22.625 --> 00:06:24.125
No, it's okay.

00:06:24.125 --> 00:06:27.708
It's not like this doesn't overlap
with my reason for coming here.

00:06:28.667 --> 00:06:30.875
I-I'm Silica.

00:06:30.875 --> 00:06:32.000
I'm Kirito.

00:06:32.000 --> 00:06:34.667
For the time being,
we'll be working together.

00:06:35.125 --> 00:06:38.250
"Floor 35: Mishe"

00:06:42.792 --> 00:06:44.500
Hey, there's Silica!

00:06:45.333 --> 00:06:48.333
You were pretty late getting back!
We were worried about you!

00:06:48.333 --> 00:06:49.167
U-Um...

00:06:49.167 --> 00:06:50.542
Let's party up sometime!

00:06:50.542 --> 00:06:52.750
We'll take you wherever
you want, okay?

00:06:52.750 --> 00:06:54.750
That's very kind of you, but...

00:06:57.542 --> 00:07:00.667
I've decided to form a party
with him for a while, so...

00:07:03.375 --> 00:07:04.958
Sorry.

00:07:07.708 --> 00:07:10.042
Sorry... to cause you trouble.

00:07:10.583 --> 00:07:11.708
Are those your fans?

00:07:12.042 --> 00:07:13.458
You're popular, huh?

00:07:13.458 --> 00:07:14.458
No...

00:07:15.917 --> 00:07:19.208
I'm sure they're just asking
me along as a mascot.

00:07:21.583 --> 00:07:25.333
Even so... when they began
to call me Dragon Tamer Silica...

00:07:26.083 --> 00:07:27.792
I let it go to my head...

00:07:27.792 --> 00:07:29.167
There's nothing to worry about.

00:07:31.125 --> 00:07:32.875
We'll make it in time.

00:07:34.792 --> 00:07:35.792
Right!

00:07:38.167 --> 00:07:40.250
Where's your home, Kirito?

00:07:40.250 --> 00:07:42.000
On Floor 50.

00:07:42.000 --> 00:07:45.042
It's a hassle, so maybe
I'll stay here tonight too.

00:07:45.042 --> 00:07:46.167
Really?

00:07:46.167 --> 00:07:49.167
The cheesecake is really good here.

00:07:49.167 --> 00:07:51.500
Well, if it isn't Silica.

00:07:52.083 --> 00:07:55.500
So... You managed to
make it out of the forest!

00:07:55.500 --> 00:07:56.667
How nice for you!

00:07:57.583 --> 00:07:58.917
Is something wrong?

00:07:58.917 --> 00:08:00.458
No, nothing.

00:08:00.458 --> 00:08:01.125
Huh?

00:08:01.125 --> 00:08:03.333
What happened to that lizard?

00:08:03.708 --> 00:08:05.042
Could it be that...

00:08:05.625 --> 00:08:07.250
Pina died.

00:08:07.250 --> 00:08:09.792
But I'm bringing it back
to life, no matter what!

00:08:11.042 --> 00:08:14.125
Meaning that you're planning
to go to the Hill of Memories...

00:08:14.500 --> 00:08:17.250
But at your level, will you
be able to clear it?

00:08:18.125 --> 00:08:19.125
Sure she will.

00:08:19.958 --> 00:08:21.750
It's not that difficult a level.

00:08:22.750 --> 00:08:25.458
You're another one who's
been seduced by this girl?

00:08:25.958 --> 00:08:28.583
You don't look particularly strong to me.

00:08:29.208 --> 00:08:30.250
Let's go.

00:08:34.250 --> 00:08:36.625
Why would she say such mean things?

00:08:37.167 --> 00:08:40.792
Is Sword Art Online your first MMO?

00:08:41.250 --> 00:08:42.167
Yes.

00:08:42.167 --> 00:08:46.292
In any online game, players often
go through personality changes.

00:08:46.292 --> 00:08:49.375
Some enjoy playing as outright villains.

00:08:50.000 --> 00:08:52.125
Our player cursors are green, right?

00:08:52.500 --> 00:08:56.500
But if you commit a crime,
your cursor will turn orange.

00:08:56.958 --> 00:08:59.208
Among them, player killers...

00:08:59.208 --> 00:09:03.292
those who've committed so-called
murders, are known as red players.

00:09:04.292 --> 00:09:05.667
Murderers... no way!

00:09:06.000 --> 00:09:09.833
In a conventional game, they could've
had fun while role-playing as the bad guy.

00:09:10.250 --> 00:09:13.542
But Sword Art Online is different.

00:09:15.958 --> 00:09:18.250
This game isn't about having fun.

00:09:19.417 --> 00:09:20.500
Kirito...

00:09:22.667 --> 00:09:23.958
I'm sorry.

00:09:26.625 --> 00:09:28.833
You're a good person, Kirito!

00:09:28.833 --> 00:09:30.667
You saved me after all!

00:09:32.833 --> 00:09:35.042
Seems like you've
cheered me up instead.

00:09:35.667 --> 00:09:37.500
Thanks, Silica.

00:09:41.042 --> 00:09:44.083
Hey! Our cheesecake is late!

00:09:44.083 --> 00:09:46.958
Excuse me, our dessert
hasn't arrived yet...

00:09:53.667 --> 00:09:56.292
If I told him I wanted
to talk a little more,

00:09:56.292 --> 00:09:57.833
would he laugh at me?

00:09:58.875 --> 00:10:01.042
Silica, are you still up?

00:10:01.042 --> 00:10:02.917
K-Kirito?

00:10:02.917 --> 00:10:06.167
I forgot to tell you
about floor 47...

00:10:06.167 --> 00:10:07.417
Want to go over it tomorrow?

00:10:07.417 --> 00:10:08.375
It's fine.

00:10:08.375 --> 00:10:10.917
I was just thinking of asking you...

00:10:14.708 --> 00:10:16.875
<i>That was close.</i>

00:10:19.875 --> 00:10:21.917
Silica, is something wrong?

00:10:21.917 --> 00:10:23.333
No, it's nothing.

00:10:23.833 --> 00:10:25.708
What's that item, Kirito?

00:10:26.250 --> 00:10:28.292
It's called a Mirage Sphere.

00:10:36.833 --> 00:10:38.333
It's so pretty!

00:10:38.708 --> 00:10:41.000
Here's floor 47's town area.

00:10:41.542 --> 00:10:42.917
And over here we have
the Hill of Memories.

00:10:43.292 --> 00:10:45.667
So we'll be following this route...

00:10:47.250 --> 00:10:48.875
Kirito--

00:10:48.875 --> 00:10:49.875
Who's there?

00:10:52.208 --> 00:10:54.292
What's going on?

00:10:54.292 --> 00:10:55.625
Someone was eavesdropping on us.

00:10:55.625 --> 00:10:59.458
B-But unless there's a knock,
you can't hear voices through a door...

00:11:00.250 --> 00:11:02.917
It's different if your listening
skill is high enough.

00:11:02.917 --> 00:11:05.375
But hardly any people have
raised their level that high.

00:11:05.750 --> 00:11:07.458
Why would they want
to eavesdrop on us?

00:11:12.667 --> 00:11:16.917
"February 24, 2024"       "Floor 47: Floria"

00:11:20.292 --> 00:11:22.167
It's like a dreamland!

00:11:22.542 --> 00:11:25.333
This floor is known as
the Flower Garden.

00:11:25.333 --> 00:11:27.625
The entire level is covered in flowers.

00:11:37.917 --> 00:11:39.042
<i>This place is...</i>

00:11:45.292 --> 00:11:46.250
Silica?

00:11:46.250 --> 00:11:47.083
Yes!

00:11:47.083 --> 00:11:48.833
Sorry to keep you waiting.

00:11:48.833 --> 00:11:49.542
What's wrong?

00:11:49.542 --> 00:11:51.500
Ah, nothing at all...

00:11:51.500 --> 00:11:52.500
Let's go.

00:11:53.833 --> 00:11:54.833
Right...

00:11:58.625 --> 00:11:59.792
What's this?

00:11:59.958 --> 00:12:04.167
If anything unexpected happens,
and I tell you to warp out,

00:12:04.167 --> 00:12:07.542
use this crystal to
jump to any town.

00:12:07.542 --> 00:12:08.625
But...

00:12:08.625 --> 00:12:09.625
Promise me.

00:12:11.333 --> 00:12:12.458
All right.

00:12:14.667 --> 00:12:16.167
Okay, let's get going.

00:12:16.167 --> 00:12:18.958
If we take this path, it will
lead us to the Hill of Memories.

00:12:29.125 --> 00:12:30.375
Um, Kirito...

00:12:39.875 --> 00:12:42.500
Calm down, Silica!
This one's really weak!

00:12:42.917 --> 00:12:46.833
K-Kirito, save me!
Don't look, but save me!

00:12:46.833 --> 00:12:48.750
--That's impossible.
--Don't look!

00:12:49.042 --> 00:12:50.792
D-Darn you...

00:12:50.792 --> 00:12:53.083
Enough is enough!

00:13:08.042 --> 00:13:09.083
Did you see anything?

00:13:10.292 --> 00:13:11.292
No, nothing.

00:13:13.583 --> 00:13:17.625
Kirito, could I ask you
about your sister?

00:13:18.333 --> 00:13:19.417
Why now, all of a sudden?

00:13:20.042 --> 00:13:22.833
You said I look like her, remember?

00:13:23.458 --> 00:13:26.000
I know it's impolite to ask
about the real world.

00:13:26.833 --> 00:13:28.083
Do you mind?

00:13:28.750 --> 00:13:32.458
I called her my little sister,
but she's actually my cousin.

00:13:34.000 --> 00:13:38.292
We grew up together since she was born,
so I'm sure she doesn't know.

00:13:38.833 --> 00:13:40.208
Maybe that's why...

00:13:40.208 --> 00:13:42.500
I've been distancing myself from her.

00:13:43.375 --> 00:13:45.208
Our grandfather's really strict.

00:13:45.833 --> 00:13:50.250
When I was eight, he made us
attend a local kendo dojo.

00:13:50.667 --> 00:13:52.167
I stopped after two years.

00:13:52.792 --> 00:13:54.917
My grandfather sure
beat me up for that.

00:13:54.917 --> 00:13:56.125
That's terrible...

00:13:56.625 --> 00:14:00.958
My sister defended me by saying that
she'd put in enough effort for both of us,

00:14:00.958 --> 00:14:02.167
so stop hitting me.

00:14:03.125 --> 00:14:07.000
After that, she really trained hard,
and made it to the nationals.

00:14:07.417 --> 00:14:09.000
That's amazing.

00:14:10.125 --> 00:14:13.375
But I always felt bad about it.

00:14:13.917 --> 00:14:17.750
She may resent me because she had
to give up what she really wanted to do.

00:14:18.750 --> 00:14:24.458
So it's possible that I'm helping you because it
feels like a way to make amends to my sister.

00:14:25.417 --> 00:14:26.417
I'm sorry.

00:14:27.333 --> 00:14:31.333
I don't think that your
sister ever hated you.

00:14:32.000 --> 00:14:35.167
No one could work that hard
for something they don't even like.

00:14:35.167 --> 00:14:38.000
She must really love kendo!

00:14:39.333 --> 00:14:41.958
You've been comforting
me all this time.

00:14:43.042 --> 00:14:44.292
Maybe you're right.

00:14:44.708 --> 00:14:45.917
I hope so.

00:14:48.500 --> 00:14:51.542
Okay... I'm gonna do my best too!

00:14:56.833 --> 00:14:58.583
Kirito...

00:15:03.083 --> 00:15:04.083
Ow!

00:15:12.917 --> 00:15:15.333
This is where the
flower of revival is?

00:15:15.333 --> 00:15:16.875
Yeah, if I'm not mistaken...

00:15:40.417 --> 00:15:41.917
Go on. Take it.

00:15:45.167 --> 00:15:46.000
"Pneuma Flower"

00:15:48.208 --> 00:15:50.333
This will bring Pina back to life, right?

00:15:50.750 --> 00:15:51.917
Yeah.

00:15:51.917 --> 00:15:53.208
I'm so glad...

00:15:53.208 --> 00:15:56.042
But there are lots of strong
monsters around here.

00:15:56.042 --> 00:15:58.167
Let's revive it after
we get back to town.

00:15:58.167 --> 00:16:00.292
I'm sure that Pina would
prefer it that way too.

00:16:00.875 --> 00:16:02.083
Yeah.

00:16:08.583 --> 00:16:09.667
Kirito?

00:16:09.667 --> 00:16:12.542
Whoever's lying in wait
there, show yourself!

00:16:16.375 --> 00:16:18.125
R-Rosalia?

00:16:18.125 --> 00:16:20.500
If you can see through
my hiding skill,

00:16:20.500 --> 00:16:23.667
your detection skill must be
quite high, swordsman.

00:16:23.958 --> 00:16:28.750
It appears that your attempts to acquire
the Pneuma Flower were successful.

00:16:29.125 --> 00:16:30.458
Congratulations.

00:16:31.042 --> 00:16:33.542
Now hand it over immediately.

00:16:33.833 --> 00:16:35.792
Wh-What are you talking about?

00:16:35.792 --> 00:16:38.250
That's not going to
happen, Rosalia.

00:16:38.250 --> 00:16:44.083
Or should I say leader of the
orange guild, Titan's Hand.

00:16:45.625 --> 00:16:47.833
But Rosalia is green!

00:16:48.208 --> 00:16:50.000
It's a simple trick.

00:16:50.000 --> 00:16:51.917
The green members find targets,

00:16:52.500 --> 00:16:55.583
and lure them to where the
orange players are lying in wait.

00:16:56.292 --> 00:17:00.708
That was one of your comrades
eavesdropping on us last night, right?

00:17:00.708 --> 00:17:04.208
Then the reason we were in the
same party for the past two weeks...

00:17:05.000 --> 00:17:08.417
That's right. I was assessing
the party's strength,

00:17:08.417 --> 00:17:11.083
while waiting for you all to earn
money from adventures.

00:17:13.375 --> 00:17:16.042
You were the prey I was
most anticipating.

00:17:16.042 --> 00:17:17.708
It was unfortunate that you left,

00:17:17.708 --> 00:17:20.167
but then you said you were
getting a rare item.

00:17:20.750 --> 00:17:23.958
Still, you knew all that
and went with her anyway?

00:17:24.333 --> 00:17:25.625
Are you an idiot?

00:17:25.625 --> 00:17:27.875
Or did she really seduce you?

00:17:28.958 --> 00:17:31.167
No, neither of those apply.

00:17:31.167 --> 00:17:33.917
I've also been searching
for you, Rosalia.

00:17:34.792 --> 00:17:36.125
What are you talking about?

00:17:36.625 --> 00:17:40.167
Ten days ago, you attacked
a guild called the Silver Flags.

00:17:40.500 --> 00:17:43.083
Four people, all but
the leader, were killed.

00:17:43.083 --> 00:17:45.792
Oh, you mean those players
with no money...

00:17:45.792 --> 00:17:51.125
Their leader was at the warp-point plaza
on the front lines, from morning till night,

00:17:51.125 --> 00:17:54.625
tearfully seeking someone
to avenge his party.

00:17:55.625 --> 00:17:58.042
But he didn't want you killed...

00:17:58.042 --> 00:18:00.292
He asked that you be sent to prison.

00:18:01.083 --> 00:18:03.375
Do you have any idea how he felt?

00:18:03.708 --> 00:18:05.083
No, not at all.

00:18:05.083 --> 00:18:07.375
What kind of idiot would
take this seriously?

00:18:07.750 --> 00:18:12.667
There's no proof that killing someone
here means they die in real life.

00:18:12.667 --> 00:18:16.250
Anyway, shouldn't you be more
concerned for yourselves?

00:18:25.958 --> 00:18:28.250
Kirito, there are too
many of them!

00:18:28.250 --> 00:18:29.667
We should run!

00:18:29.667 --> 00:18:30.833
It's all right.

00:18:30.833 --> 00:18:32.542
Until I tell you to run,

00:18:32.542 --> 00:18:34.833
just keep the crystal ready.
Stay put and watch.

00:18:34.833 --> 00:18:35.750
Okay.

00:18:35.750 --> 00:18:36.875
B-But...

00:18:38.125 --> 00:18:39.292
Kirito!

00:18:39.875 --> 00:18:41.417
Kirito?

00:18:41.417 --> 00:18:42.875
Dressed all in black...

00:18:43.167 --> 00:18:45.083
A one-handed, no-shield style.

00:18:45.083 --> 00:18:47.542
Don't tell me that's
the Black Swordsman...

00:18:48.042 --> 00:18:52.500
Rosalia, this is the beater
who solos the front lines...

00:18:52.500 --> 00:18:53.625
He's on an Assault Team!

00:18:53.625 --> 00:18:55.125
An Assault Team?

00:18:55.708 --> 00:18:59.250
Why would someone from an Assault
Team be all the way down here?

00:18:59.250 --> 00:19:02.417
Come on! Just take him out already!
And take everything he owns!

00:19:02.417 --> 00:19:03.708
Die!

00:19:12.375 --> 00:19:15.167
I've got to save him... Kirito...

00:19:20.000 --> 00:19:21.125
What's going on?

00:19:28.250 --> 00:19:31.208
You fools... What are
you doing? Just kill him!

00:19:32.667 --> 00:19:35.125
About 400, in around 10 seconds...

00:19:35.750 --> 00:19:39.250
That's the total damage you
seven can inflict on me.

00:19:40.458 --> 00:19:42.583
I'm level 78.

00:19:42.583 --> 00:19:45.125
I have 14,500 HP.

00:19:45.125 --> 00:19:47.917
My battle-healing skill auto-regenerates

00:19:47.917 --> 00:19:50.125
600 points every 10 seconds.

00:19:50.750 --> 00:19:53.208
We could stand here all day,
and you'd never beat me.

00:19:54.250 --> 00:19:55.542
Is that even possible?

00:19:55.542 --> 00:19:56.750
It is.

00:19:56.750 --> 00:19:59.792
High enough numbers will
give you a ridiculous advantage...

00:20:00.375 --> 00:20:03.250
That's what makes MMOs that
use a level system so unfair.

00:20:04.792 --> 00:20:09.250
My client spent his entire fortune
to buy this warp crystal.

00:20:09.958 --> 00:20:12.458
It's set to send you to the prison area.

00:20:13.083 --> 00:20:15.583
I'm sending every one of you there!

00:20:16.833 --> 00:20:19.917
I'm green, so if you hurt me,
you'll go orange...

00:20:26.167 --> 00:20:28.500
Just so we're clear, I'm a solo player.

00:20:28.500 --> 00:20:31.833
One or two days of playing while
orange mean nothing to me.

00:20:38.667 --> 00:20:40.250
Sorry, Silica...

00:20:40.708 --> 00:20:43.333
I ended up using you
as bait, more or less.

00:20:43.958 --> 00:20:46.542
I thought you'd be scared
if I told you the truth.

00:20:48.792 --> 00:20:52.750
You're a good person,
so I would never be scared.

00:20:54.750 --> 00:20:57.583
So you're leaving after all?

00:20:58.042 --> 00:21:01.125
Yeah, I've been away from the
front lines for five days...

00:21:01.833 --> 00:21:03.333
I need to get back right away.

00:21:04.458 --> 00:21:07.667
I-It's amazing that you're
on an Assault Team!

00:21:08.042 --> 00:21:11.333
I could try for years
and never get that far.

00:21:13.292 --> 00:21:15.750
Um... I...

00:21:15.750 --> 00:21:17.583
Levels are just numbers.

00:21:18.042 --> 00:21:21.458
Strength in this world
is just an illusion.

00:21:22.000 --> 00:21:25.167
There are more important
things than that.

00:21:27.000 --> 00:21:29.000
Next time, let's meet in the real world.

00:21:29.417 --> 00:21:32.625
Then we can be friends,
just like we are now.

00:21:34.833 --> 00:21:35.875
Right.

00:21:35.875 --> 00:21:38.167
We will! For sure!

00:21:38.667 --> 00:21:40.958
Okay, let's revive Pina.

00:21:40.958 --> 00:21:42.000
Yeah!

00:21:44.875 --> 00:21:45.625
"Pina's Heart"

00:21:50.583 --> 00:21:51.792
"Pneuma Flower"

00:21:55.583 --> 00:21:57.000
<i>Pina...</i>

00:21:57.000 --> 00:22:00.500
<i>I'll talk to you lots and lots, okay?</i>

00:22:02.583 --> 00:22:04.917
<i>About my amazing adventure today...</i>

00:22:11.042 --> 00:22:16.292
<i>And about the one day in my life</i>
<i>that I had a big brother.</i>

00:22:30.083 --> 00:22:41.583
<i>The tolling of the faraway bells</i>
<i>sounded a little lonely to me</i>

00:22:41.917 --> 00:22:53.417
<i>So I tried harder, one more time,</i>
<i>this time soaring higher, all the way up</i>

00:22:53.792 --> 00:22:59.333
<i>Neither this reality that just keeps repeating itself</i>

00:22:59.667 --> 00:23:05.167
<i>Nor all my wishes, as numerous as the stars</i>

00:23:05.583 --> 00:23:10.583
<i>Now that I've found the tomorrow</i>
<i>I should strive for</i>

00:23:10.917 --> 00:23:15.875
<i>None of them can overcome these feelings of mine</i>

00:23:16.208 --> 00:23:22.708
<i>A world without end, opening up before my eyes</i>

00:23:23.042 --> 00:23:26.667
<i>Even if it's no more than a dream</i>

00:23:27.208 --> 00:23:33.917
<i>Even if I'm still lost, deep in my heart, it is strong</i>

00:23:34.250 --> 00:23:39.708
<i>Echoing forever and ever</i>

00:23:40.042 --> 00:23:46.250
<i>Shining softly, ever so softly</i>

00:23:47.042 --> 00:23:53.152
Next Time: "Murder in the Safe Zone."
